rComments: His quizzes and midterm are very simple and it is easy to do well. He's super interesting and often gives s during class instead of focusing solely on the material. He's very engaging and especially if you are taking PHY245, Michael will be extremely helpful.

He is incredibly tough to understand and he spends very little time explaining the theorems and too much time doing problems. He is interested in the material and talking about it, but seems to have no interest in actually helping you understand. You may ask for clarification, but he repeats the same thing he originally said over and over and over.
He's one of those guys that doesn't do homework in high school, but gets good grades, then grows up to be a teacher.

If you are serious about math don't take this course. You will not learn any real math from this course. All you will learn are some vague intuition. BTW, you will have to spend lots of valuable time searching around tasteless applied math models which are too naive to be useful in real world.
